<br>
1) What makes a magician a magician?<br>
<br>
Answer: A magician is a summoner. Like a Wizard is a Damage Dealer, a Necromancer is a DoTer, an Enchanter is a buffer. All these classes do what they do well.<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Fal <br>
<br>
I have to take issue with this statement because this is just false.  Magicians are a pure caster that has specialized in conjuration/summoning, just like a wizard is a class that is specialized in invocation/evocation. Necromancers specialize in undead and enchanters in crowd control.<br>
<br>
Ok the reason that my description differs from yours is because when you say wizards are specialized damage dealers and basically magicians are not is just crap. Magicians are a damage class. They just do there damage via the conjuration school of magic. Just like wizards do there damage via the evocation/invocation schools of magic.  To say that wizards are damage dealers and magicians are &quot;summoners&quot; is kinda short-sided because then you are saying there is only &quot;one&quot; damage casting class in the game??<br>
<br>
Now I know this isn't true. It would be just like saying that just because rogues are the highest damage class in the game they are the only damage melee class in the game. I rolled a mage because VI description said this was one of the top damage classes but because of that had little defense. Yes it said we were the &quot;summoners of norath&quot; but right after that it says &quot;Magicians are one of the most deadly offensive classes in the game&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
Quote:<br>
<br>
2) But I don't LIKE summoning things on raids!<br>
<br>
Answer: Then why play a summoner? Mages from the beginning have been summoners. I made a mage so I could SUMMON things, not because i wanted to be the uberest damage dealer.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Well that may be why you rolled a mage but i would have to say 98% of people that play magicians didn't roll their toon for the same reason. They made a mage because they liked being this raw offensive powered class that had no defense as a trade off.  Most of the things we summon are crap until very late and level and even then I have to question the thinking that went into such spells.  <br>
<br>
<br>
In closing magicians are a damage class and always will be. We are just a class that uses the conjuration/summoning schools of magic but that doesn't makes us any less a damage dealer. It just means we get to summon crap as our secondary skill while wizards get to port and trans.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
