<br>
Thing is, when the game came out, mages WERE the uber damage dealer.  We were kings of damage for some time -- until people started to organize raids.  High End raids to be specific.  Alot of people I've talked to at Verant didn't even expect things to go like they have -- They expected the roles the classes have in group play to be there on high end raid play.<br>
<br>
Sure, the main reason I originally made a mage isnt a good one now (summoning items wasn't all it was cracked up to be save for a few select summons)...<br>
<br>
but alot of people here have made good points...without mages, alot of big big mobs would NOT die.  If mages were the big time damage dealers instead of mod rodders on these big time raids, they wouldnt work out nearly as well.<br>
